      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "CPB hemolysis CFD applicability domain",
      "description": "Model is applicable to Newtonian blood-analog fluid with hematocrit 35–45%, pump rotational speeds 1500–3500 RPM, and flow rates 2–8 L/min. Geometry is restricted to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump (GCBP) nominal design envelope with dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm on impeller tip clearance and ±0.1 mm on volute gap. Non-Newtonian effects and cavitation are explicitly excluded from scope."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
